## 3. Frontend Folder Structure

App-level (same MFE): **`src/hooks/`** and **`src/components/`** are only for the **widest** consumer span. **`src/hooks/`** is for hooks used from **more than one** page **domain** — i.e. **two or more** distinct `src/pages/<Domain>/` trees (or the same hook shared across routes that are not one colocated page). It is **not** a default place for new logic: single-domain behavior belongs under that domain’s `features/…/hooks/`, `shared/hooks/`, or legacy `pages/<domain>/hooks/`. See scope ladder in [.cursor/skills/frontend-page-structure/SKILL.md](../skills/frontend-page-structure/SKILL.md).

**Page folder** `src/pages/<domain>/` (route root: one folder per screen, e.g. `AudioSection/AudioSection.tsx` + `index.ts` — no loose `*.tsx` next to `src/pages/<Name>/` as a file-only route). Prefer the explicit contract:

```text
pages/<domain>/
├── <Domain>.tsx          # composition-only entry
├── index.ts
├── shared/               # hooks + components reused by multiple first-class features of this page
│   ├── hooks/
│   └── components/       # PascalCase folder per widget (see gates)
├── features/             # one PascalCase folder per first-class feature; fractal inner features + component-level features allowed (see skill)
│   └── <FeatureName>/
│       ├── hooks/ | shared/ | components/ | features/   # as needed
│       └── ...
├── constants.ts | types.ts | utils/   # page-scoped
└── (legacy) hooks/ | components/     # treat as page-level shared; new work should use shared/ + features/
```

**CI (workspace root):** `npm run check:page-structure` — prints which packages include `src/pages`, then runs gates: no loose `*.tsx` as direct child of any `**/pages/**/components/`, PascalCase widget folders, valid `features/` segment names, feature `shared/components/` multi-file import span, and **per-app** [scripts/check-page-root-contract.mjs](scripts/check-page-root-contract.mjs) (Pascal `src/pages/<Domain>/` roots, no loose route files in `src/pages/`, and each domain has `features/`, `shared/hooks/`, `shared/components/`; scope is `enforcedAppBasenames` in [scripts/check-page-root-contract.json](scripts/check-page-root-contract.json), currently e.g. `gaqno-ai-ui`). App-level hooks, prop spread, and cross-page imports are not automated in these scripts.

The **full** tree, **fractal** `features/`, page vs feature `shared/`, and **scope ladder** live only in the skill — do not duplicate here.

### Rules

- A hook or component file lives at the **narrowest scope** that matches its **widest** consumer (sub-widget `hooks/` → feature `shared/hooks/` → page `shared/hooks/` → `src/hooks/` / `src/components/` — see skill **Scope ladder**).
- **One page domain only** (a single `pages/<Domain>/` tree): colocate under `pages/<domain>/features/<Feature>/…`, `…/shared/…` when several first-class features of that domain share it, or legacy `pages/<domain>/hooks/` / `components/`.
- **More than one page domain** (same MFE): promote to **`src/hooks/`** or **`src/components/`** (true app-wide reuse across domains).
- **Never** import from `pages/<A>/` into `pages/<B>/`. Lift shared code to `src/`, **`@gaqno-development/frontcore`**, or **`@gaqno-types`** as appropriate.
- UI primitives always come from `@gaqno-development/frontcore/components/ui`.

